dsas_datasource_connect_hint: To make a new connection click on the"Authorize" button.
All information about API Keys, can be found here.
To make a new connection click on the"Authorize" button.

Please use the platform API credentials here.
The platform API credentials are provided by your Account Manager.

To connect datasource we need to request <subdomain> and <API key>.
Both String inputs, required.

You can make an API request right within your browser address bar,
as long as you know your API key and the STAT subdomain that your account is on.
(For example, “app2.getstat.com” or “public3.getstat.com.”
You can see this in the address bar when you are logged into the app.)

These details are used to create an API request URL:

XML request:
- {your_app_subdomain}.getstat.com/api/v2/{your_API_key}/{request_URL_string}

JSON request:
- {your_app_subdomain}.getstat.com/api/v2/{your_API_key}/{request_URL_string}?format=json

Typical example:
- app3.getstat.com/api/v2/478gh7612456jn098hgdn972647h762t56374hg67/projects/list/

Connection to Amazon MWS platform requests to have Amazon Seller Account with Professional Seller Plan and authorize Improvado Developer Account with ID 344969540817 for NA (US, CA, MX) marketplace and ID 026718442088 for EU ( Europe) marketplace by steps:
  • The seller goes to the Manage your apps page in Seller Central and logs into their Amazon seller account as the primary account holder.
  • The seller clicks the Authorize new developer button and follows the authorization workflow.
  • The seller gets MWS Auth Token value and uses it in the field "MWS Auth Token" below.
To find the MWS Auth Token, log into Seller Central account and navigate to the User Permissions page in the Settings. Scroll to the bottom of this page and locate the Third party developer and apps section, from here click on Visit Manage Your Apps.

Improvadoio should be listed as an authorized developer on the Manage your apps page. To the right of the developer row, there is a small blue link, labeled View, under the "MWS Auth Token" column. Click on View, "MWS Auth Token" will be shown in the same cell.

Connection to Amazon MWS platform requests to have Amazon Seller Account with Professional Seller Plan and authorize Improvado Developer Account with ID 344969540817 for NA (US, CA, MX) marketplace and ID 026718442088 for EU ( Europe) marketplace by steps:
  • The seller goes to the Manage your apps page in Seller Central and logs into their Amazon seller account as the primary account holder.
  • The seller clicks the Authorize new developer button and follows the authorization workflow.
  • The seller gets MWS Auth Token value and uses it in the field "MWS Auth Token" below.
To find the MWS Auth Token, log into Seller Central account and navigate to the User Permissions page in the Settings. Scroll to the bottom of this page and locate the Third party developer and apps section, from here click on Visit Manage Your Apps.

Improvadoio should be listed as an authorized developer on the Manage your apps page. To the right of the developer row, there is a small blue link, labeled View, under the "MWS Auth Token" column. Click on View, "MWS Auth Token" will be shown in the same cell.

Both String inputs, required.

You can make an API request right within your browser address bar,
as long as you know your API key and the STAT subdomain that your account is on.
(For example, “app2.getstat.com” or “public3.getstat.com.”
You can see this in the address bar when you are logged into the app.)

These details are used to create an API request URL:

XML request:
- {your_app_subdomain}.getstat.com/api/v2/{your_API_key}/{request_URL_string}

JSON request:
- {your_app_subdomain}.getstat.com/api/v2/{your_API_key}/{request_URL_string}?format=json

Typical example:
- app3.getstat.com/api/v2/478gh7612456jn098hgdn972647h762t56374hg67/projects/list/

  • The seller goes to the Manage your apps page in Seller Central and logs into their Amazon seller account as the primary account holder.
  • The seller clicks the Authorize new developer button and follows the authorization workflow.
  • The seller gets MWS Auth Token value and uses it in the field "MWS Auth Token" below.
To find the MWS Auth Token, log into Seller Central account and navigate to the User Permissions page in the Settings. Scroll to the bottom of this page and locate the Third party developer and apps section, from here click on Visit Manage Your Apps.

Improvadoio should be listed as an authorized developer on the Manage your apps page. To the right of the developer row, there is a small blue link, labeled View, under the "MWS Auth Token" column. Click on View, "MWS Auth Token" will be shown in the same cell.
